I have updated the forms section to support Hidden Input fields. This new field type allows you to set a static value (or use auto-fill from contact data) that will be included in the form submission without being visible to the user filling out the form.

Key Changes:
Forms Editor (FormsView.jsx):

Added "Hidden Input" as a new field type.
When the "Hidden Input" type is selected, a new "Static Value" field appears. You can enter any constant value here that you want to send with every submission (e.g., a source ID, a campaign name, or a secret key).
Auto-fill also works with hidden fields, allowing you to automatically pass contact details (like their CRM ID) to your webhook without cluttering the UI.
Form Runner (ContextWidget.jsx):

Updated the form runner to automatically include these hidden fields in the JSON payload sent to your endpoint.
Hidden fields are gracefully skipped during rendering so they don't appear in the contact's dynamic form panel.
Example Use Case:
If you need every form submission to include source: "google-voice", you can now add a field with:

Display Label: Source (only visible to you in the editor)
Payload Key: source
Type: Hidden Input
Static Value: google-voice
When the form is submitted, the JSON will automatically include "source": "google-voice".

